HEADWORD: Topographer
<hw>To*pog"ra*pher</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>topographe</ets>, Cr. <?/ .]</ety> <def>One who is skilled in the
science of topography; one who describes a particular place, town, city,
or tract of land.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Dante is the one authorized <qex>topographer</qex> of the
mediaeval hell.</q> <rj><qau>Milman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Topographical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Topographic</ent>⟦br⟧
